name: HKFitzpatrickSkinType
desc: Categories representing the user’s skin type based on the Fitzpatrick scale.

items.name: case notSet
items.desc: Either the user’s skin type is not set, or the user has not granted your app permission to read the skin type.

items.name: case I
items.desc: Pale white skin that always burns easily in the sun and never tans.

items.name: case II
items.desc: White skin that burns easily and tans minimally.

items.name: case III
items.desc: White to light brown skin that burns moderately and tans uniformly.

items.name: case IV
items.desc: Beige-olive, lightly tanned skin that burns minimally and tans moderately.

items.name: case V
items.desc: Brown skin that rarely burns and tans profusely.

items.name: case VI
items.desc: Dark brown to black skin that never burns and tans profusely.
